#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration by using Combustion"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes Combustion&dash;the tool used to configure your "
"system according to your configuration on first boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "About Combustion"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Combustion is a dracut module that enables you to configure your system on "
"first boot. Combustion reads a provided <filename>script</filename> and "
"executes commands in it and thus perform changes to the file system. You can "
"use Combustion to change the default partitions, set users' passwords, "
"create files, install packages, etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Combustion dracut module is invoked after the <literal>ignition."
"firstboot</literal> argument is passed to the kernel command line. "
"Combustion then reads configuration from <filename>script</filename> . If "
"the network flag has been found in <filename>script</filename> , Combustion "
"tries to configure network. After <literal>/sysroot</literal> is mounted, "
"Combustion tries to activate all mountpoints in <filename>/etc/fstab</"
"filename> and then call the <command>transactional-update</command> to apply "
"other changes (like setting &rootuser; password or install packages)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using Combustion, you need to label the configuration device to "
"<literal>combustion</literal> , create a specific directory structure in "
"your configuration media and include a configuration named <filename>script</"
"filename> . In the root directory create a directory&dash; "
"<filename>combustion</filename> and place the <filename>script</filename> "
"into this directory along with other files&mdash;SSH key, configuration "
"files, etc. The directory structure then should look as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    &lt;root directory&gt;\n"
"\t- combustion\n"
"\t\t- script\n"
"\t\t- other files\n"
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tYou can use Combustion to configure your QEMU/KVM virtual machine. In this "
"case, pass the location of the <filename>script</filename> by using the "
"<literal>fw_cfg</literal> parameter of the <command>qemu</command> command:\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"\t-fw_cfg name=opt/org.opensuse.combustion/script,file=/var/combustion-"
"script\n"
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tCombustion can be used along with Ignition. If you intend to do so, label "
"your configuration media <literal>ignition</literal> and include the "
"<filename>ignition</filename> directory with the <filename>config.ign</"
"filename> to your directory structure as shown below:\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&lt;root directory&gt;\n"
"\t-combustion\n"
"\t\t- script\n"
"\t\t- other files\n"
"\t- ignition \n"
"\t\t- config.ign\n"
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this case Ignition runs before Combustion."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>script</filename> configuration file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>script</filename> configuration file is a set of commands that "
"are executed on your system in a transactional-update shell. This section "
"provides ecxamples how to perform various configuration tasks by using "
"Combustion."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As the <filename>script</filename> file is interpreted by bash, make sure to "
"include the interpreteur declaration at the beginning:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" #!/bin/sh\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The minimum configuration must include the &rootuser; password. Make sure to "
"configure a secure password. In case you use a randomly generated password, "
"use at least 10 characters. If you create your password manually, use even "
"more than 10 characters and combine uppercase and lowecase letters, and "
"numbers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you want to configure network during the first boot, add the "
"following statement to your <filename>script</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" # combustion: network\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this statement will pass the <literal>rd.neednet=1</literal> argument "
"to dracut. If you do not use the statement, the default <literal>dhcp</"
"literal> will be used on all available interfaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting a password for &rootuser;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you set the &rootuser; password, generate a hash of the password, e."
"g. by using the <command>openssl passwd -6</command> . In our example the "
"hash of <emphasis>password4root</emphasis> has been used. To set the "
"password, add the following to your <filename>script</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" echo 'root:$5$.wn2BZHlEJ5R3B1C$TAHEchlU.h2tvfOpOki54NaHpGYKwdNhjaBuSpDotD7' "
"| chpasswd -e\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding SSH keys"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following snippet creates a directory to store the &rootuser;'s SSH key "
"and then copies the public SSH key located on the configuration device to "
"the <filename>authorized_keys</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" mkdir -pm700 /root/.ssh/\n"
"cat id_rsa_new.pub &gt;&gt; /root/.ssh/authorized_keys\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The SSH service must be enabled in case you need to use remote login via "
"SSH. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-script-services\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some services need to enabled to use &slema; properly, e.g. to enable the "
"SSH service, add the following line to <filename>script</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" systemctl enable sshd.service\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing packages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the first boot configuration you can install additional packages to "
"your system, e.g. the <literal>vim</literal> editor by adding:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" zypper --non-interactive install vim-small\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_combustion.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bear in mind that you will not be able to use <command>zypper</command> "
"after the configuration is complete and you boot to the configured system. "
"To perform changes later, you must use the <command>transactional-update</"
"command> command to create an changed snapshot. For details, refer to."
msgstr ""
